Package: grub-gfxboot
Architecture: darwin-i386 freebsd-i386 hurd-i386 kfreebsd-i386 knetbsd-i386 i386 netbsd-i386 openbsd-i386 amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Provides: grub
Replaces: grub
Conflicts: grub
Suggests: grub-gfxboot-disk, grub-gfxboot-doc, gfxboot, grubconf
Description: GRand Unified Bootloader
 GRUB is a GPLed bootloader with graphical menu patches and reiser4 support
 intended to unify bootloading across x86 operating systems.  In addition
 to loading the Linux kernel,
 it implements the Multiboot standard, which allows for flexible loading
 of multiple boot images (needed for modular kernels such as the GNU Hurd).
 .
 This version of grub is patched to do shiny stuff like display graphical
 menus using the gfxboot patches and support for the experimental reiser4
 filesystem. It might also eat the cat.

Package: grub-gfxboot-disk
Architecture: all
Provides: grub-disk
Replaces: grub-disk
Conflicts: grub-disk
Suggests: grub-gfxboot-doc
Description: GRUB bootable disk image
 This package contains a GRUB rescue disk. It consists of a bootable
 1.44 floppy image you can use to grab a rescue disk or be run in an
 i386 emulator, like Bochs.

Package: grub-gfxboot-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Provides: grub-doc
Replaces: grub-doc
Conflicts: grub-doc
Suggests: grub-gfxboot-disk
Description: Documentation for GRand Unified Bootloader
 GRUB is a GPLed bootloader with graphical menu patches and reiser4 support 
 intended to unify bootloading across x86 operating systems.  In addition to 
 loading the Linux kernel, it implements the Multiboot standard, which allows 
 for flexible loading of multiple boot images (needed for modular kernels 
 such as the GNU Hurd).
